From 8d65e3026441c8c13d178a4123cedbe56c37faf5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: YUKIN <sandeshchhetrii038@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2026 13:56:31 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add admin Appearance controls: theme colors + homepage
 section layout

- New /admin/appearance page: admins can pick a primary and accent brand
  color (theme-colors.ts derives the actual shades used across the site
  from those two picks) and show/hide + reorder homepage sections below
  the hero (Featured Rooms, Amenities, Dining, Spa, Testimonials,
  Gallery, FAQ).
- Colors are wired through CSS custom properties on <html> in the root
  layout, read by tailwind.config.ts, so the whole site repaints from
  the existing bg-conservatory-*/text-bronze-* utility classes with no
  per-component changes.
- Reuses the existing generic content-section save pipeline (new
  "appearance" entry in CONTENT_SECTIONS/content-defaults.ts), so it
  gets auth, validation, and activity logging for free.
- Homepage now renders its optional sections from
  appearance.homeSections order/visibility instead of a fixed list.
